        <section id="header">
          <div class="page-header">
            <h1><%_i%>3. Header<%/i%></h1>
          </div>
          <p class="lead">The header contain a minimal of information, to keep it simpel and clear to the user. Page name, witchs can easily been edit, just by clicking the text. Here you also have the ability to change language. In the right side of the header 2 buttons are showen, Preview and Publish. The preview button opens a new page with the current page. The Publish button is saving and publishing the current page. Umbraco is constantly saving the current document in the background, so you don't need to press save, but you can still access the Save button by clicking the arrow down, besides Publish. All header will always be visible to the user.</p>
          <img src="assets/img/umbraco/header.gif" alt="Header">

        </section>

